Permissions apply to three distinct groups:
u (User/Owner)
g (Group)(shares access rights)
o (Others)(Public)
There are three basic access types:
r (Read): Value = 4
w (Write): Value = 2
x (Execute): Value = 1
You use a three-digit code. 
Each digit is the sum of the permissions for User, Group, and Others.
chmod 755 file.sh
7 (4+2+1): Owner can read, write, execute.
5 (4+1): Group can read, execute.
5 (4+1): Others can read, execute.

